Azure vs AWS Chaos Monkey Analysis

Component Comparison 

+-------------------------+----------------------------+
|  ++ Azure Version ++    |     ++ AWS Version ++      |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 
| Azure Virtual Machines  |            EC2             |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 
|      Functions          |          Lambda            |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 
|  Azure AutoScaling      |     AutoScaling Rules      |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 
|   Availablilty Sets     |    Autoscaling Groups      |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 
|  Azure Active Directory |           IAM              |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 
|    Notification Hubs    |           SNS              |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 
|  Service Bus Messaging  |           SQS              |
+-------------------------+----------------------------+ 

aws CLI vs azure CLI
boto3 vs azure SDKs

For Azure App Service, select an App Service Plan that offers multiple instances. 
For Azure Cloud Services, configure each of your roles to use multiple instances. 
For Azure Virtual Machines (VMs), ensure that your VM architecture includes more than one VM and that each VM is included in an availability set.

Azure Checking functions for health checks (Azure application insights)
AWS health/readiness checks (CloudWatch event logs)

Scale sets in Azure do state that they replicate the AutoScaling features of AWS but unable to prove this. 